node.text:
If I’ve learned anything from my students, it’s that they do not like being inside of a boring classroom – and that can be even more challenging when that classroom is virtual. In a continued effort to keep young minds engaged, and in recognition of #NationalDistanceLearningWeek, I kicked off a very cool project with my students that engages them using technology.

We’ve been talking about STEM learning through @3m Science at Home, so I’ve given them the task of starting their own podcast, where they will fuse technology and critical thinking skills to share new information with the world. Are you as excited as I am to see what they create?! #science #STEM #scienceathome

Teacher Tip Friday!

Reading is something that we do daily. Whether it’s scanning on social media or discovering a new book, reading truly is fundamental.

Having your students/children analyze the characters in a story is beneficial. Students will learn how to study different perspectives and practice an important skill called “inferencing”. Inferencing is when you use evidence and reasoning to arrive at a conclusion. Have some fun with it!

Lately I have been asking myself how can I bring more value to the people I serve daily. Not the forced “I’m posting this product to beat the algorithm”, but a genuine perspective. I think I’ve figured that out.

Sunday talks are meant to give a fresh perspective from Michael Bonner. Friday’s will be designated tips for educators from Mr.Bonner. Same person, but two different roles. Even if you aren’t a teacher, I’m sure you will be able to gain something from Teacher Tip Fridays!

This has been a long week for some of you. The mental and psychological turmoil you are feeling because of the untimely death of #AhmaudArbery can drain you. Please know I’m praying for you, be gentle with yourself, and we will rise up strong. 	#legacyoverlikes #elevate #embraceit #teachersofinstagram #education #childrensbook #bonnerville #technology 	#teachersfollowteachers #rcainspired #philanthropy #middleschool #elementaryeducation #bebetter #entreprenuer 	#teacher #allinforteachers #fundteachers #gethappyhour #teacherappreciationday

The love you feel as you watch this video is the strength that runs through my veins. 

For the month of August 2021 I will be on the road 26 out of 31 days. I came home this weekend to recharge myself with love from my family. 

Education and the application of knowledge is the great equalizer in our society. There are times when I go into different cities where my message of inclusivity and innovation isn’t welcomed. Although it can be anticipated, at times it can still drain you. When I come home, my mental and emotional stature straightens up. Im reminded of my purpose. 

More importantly, I understand that this young man from the #252 (Eastern North Carolina) has something powerful to say. Something that will ensure students all across the world are seen, heard, and that space is created to let their brilliance shine. 

I’m charged up now. 

Let’s go to work 😤

#legacyoverlikes  #embraceit #teachersofinstagram #bonnerville #bebetter

Let’s Talk:

Jamaica is special to me. 

It was my first international solo trip in 2016 with @goldstampz company. During that time my divorce was just finalized, I finished a ROUGH 3rd year of teaching, and the time I spent in isolation rediscovering myself was coming to a close. My net-worth was -$159,979 🥴. While I was in Montego Bay, I remember going to the beach and praying that better days were ahead. 5 months after that trip, the prayers I said in Jamaica began to happen in my life.

Now on today, you can see why a “return” to Jamiaca is so meaningful to me. Because of where I was at in 2016, I wanted to treat myself unapologetically. I  intentionally wanted to celebrate my growth, perseverance, and vision to help others. I live a life of service and I’m aware that you can burnout if you don’t take care of yourself. I even decided to select a room that was perfect for me. (Trust me, the penthouse at The Royalton in Negril didn’t disappoint 🔥.) I spent numerous moments on the balcony reflecting on where I’ve been, where I am, and where I’m going. 

This long caption isn’t for everyone, but for a select few. This is for those who know you are destined for greatness, but that “moment” hasn’t happened yet. My life today is a manifestation of prayers, written goals, and execution that was initiated 5 years at VIEWS. Wherever you are and however you are doing, know that better days are coming. 

That’s not toxic positivity, but my life story. 

Watch what I pull off in the next 5 years 😤.

Keep pushing family 🤎

node.text:
My parents are celebrating their 38th wedding anniversary on today. My mother called me last night FULL of excitement because my father is taking her to @ruthschris for the first time. That phone call filled my heart with joy. 

God gave me the perfect set of parents. I wouldn’t be this humble and successful if it wasn’t for them. Now that they have sacrificed so much for my siblings and I, it’s their time to live life to the fullest.

That is why for their wedding anniversary gift, I’m going to fly them out of the country for their first international trip ✈️. (I will be sure to document that for those who are inspired to do the same.) 

Happy Anniversary Michael and Freda Bonner. 

I love you to the furthest galaxy and back🤎

I’m heading to the airport and tomorrow will be my first speech “in person” since August 2020. That’s 10 months without the electric energy that comes from a live crowd 🔥. Things have changed, but I’m excited to get back out on the road. 

Also, this month is the beginning of my 4th year as a public speaker. 

I’m grateful:
- to serve and help others. 
- for longevity as we continue to navigate through Covid-19. 
- for the tenacity to keep students as the sole focus of my mission and platform. 
- and for my family and community. 🤎

Tomorrow will be amazing in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina and I believe the rest of your week will be too. Stay safe and keep pushing family.
